[thinking] **Evaluating dynamic-access calls**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm considering how dynamic-access class report call sites might not necessarily fail. If we add a test that invokes it reflectively under native without metadata, I'm wondering if it may fail unless native can resolve the public method reflectively, provided it's registered. I think it’s critical to inspect existing metadata to see if it includes methods from ExtensionRegistryFactory. There’s a lot to unpack here, but clarity will help.
